						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar of the rock-cut cave temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarman Sundara-Chōḷapāṇḍya year 8: 1028-29 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription seems to record a gift of land for maintaining a lamp in the temple of Kayilāyattu-Perumāṉaḍigaḷ at Vīravinōdachaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Kallaga-nāḍu in Muḍigoṇḍaśōḻavaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						<p>The donor's name is not clear. However, from the extant portion of the record, it may be said that the above gift was made by Maṇḍai ••• śōlai Śāttaṉ of the above village. The names of the Śivabrāhmaṇas, who are probably to carry out this endowment are given.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIV, No. 136.</p>						

						</summary>
